In this blog post, we delve into the motivations behind Fromager and explain its unique role in the ecosystem.

Reproducibility across platforms: When you manage multiple variants (x86_64, aarch64, CPU-only, CUDA), you need the same packages built consistently across all of them.

And there's no way to manage multiple platform variants (CPU, CUDA, ROCm) from a single build pipeline.
